headline: Seagate, Western Digital Stocks Stay Red-Hot Ahead Of Earnings. What To Know.
summary: Seagate Technology and Western Digital stocks climbed higher again Monday, adding to a triple-digit rally.

headline: Tradr to Launch Leveraged ETFs on LITE, SNDK and WDC
summary: Tradr ETFs, a provider of ETFs designed for sophisticated investors and professional traders, announced that it expects to launch three new single stock leveraged ETFs on Tuesday, January 27. The funds will be listed on Cboe and all three represent first-to-market strategies. Each ETF aims to deliver twice (200%) the daily performance of its specific underlying stock.

headline: Western Digital (WDC) Stock Is Up, What You Need To Know
summary: Shares of leading data storage manufacturer Western Digital (NASDAQ: WDC) jumped 3.7% in the morning session after an analyst at Cantor Fitzgerald increased their price target on the stock.

headline: Nvidia’s Rally Shows DeepSeek Fears Were Unfounded a Year Later
summary: DeepSeek erased a record $589 billion from Nvidia Corp.’s market value in one day after the company revealed an AI model thought to be comparable to those of OpenAI and Meta Platforms Inc. and developed at a fraction of the cost.  Nvidia’s double-digit plunge led the S&P 500 Index 1.5% lower, while the tech heavy Nasdaq 100 Index shed 3%.

headline: Sandisk Stock Is Up 1,000% in 6 Months. Analysts Think It Can Gain Another 20% from Here.
summary: SNDK stock has been on a tear higher over the past six months, but analysts still see upside to a Street-high price target of $580.

headline: Quantum ActiveScale & Telestream DIVA Build Sustainable Media Archives
summary: QMCO teams up with Telestream to certify DIVA on ActiveScale storage as it targets $67M Q3 revenue, backed by a $25M backlog and debt reset.
